Function Reference/is network admin « WordPress Codex
-----------

This [Conditional Tag](/Conditional_Tags "Conditional Tags") checks
whether the current request if for a network admin screen
(wp-admin/network). This is a boolean function, meaning it returns
either TRUE or FALSE.

Usage
-----

` <?php is_network_admin(); ?> `

Parameters
----------

This tag does not accept any parameters.

Return Values
-------------

 `(boolean)` 
:   True on success, false on failure.

Examples
--------

    if ( is_network_admin() ) {
        echo "You are viewing a WordPress network administration page";
    } else {
        echo "You are <em>not</em> viewing a WordPress network administration page";
    }

Notes
-----

`is_network_admin()` does not inform on whether the user is a super
admin or has network administration rights.

Change Log
----------

Since: 1.3.0

Source File
-----------

`is_network_admin()` is located in `wp-includes/load.php`.

